12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
14 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 5-13.1 of Title 2, unless there
15 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
16 A. The Oklahoma Department of Agriculture, Food, and Forestry
17 shall operate an Ag in the Classroom Education Program for the
18 purpose of educating students about agriculture within this state.
19 B. The Ag in the Classroom Education Program shall:
20 1. Develop curriculum for students in grades kindergarten
21 through twelve for Ag in the Classroom programs in urban and rural
22 schools;
23 2. Provide training and workshops for teachers who utilize Ag
24 in the Classroom curriculum;
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB1410 SFLR Page 1
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 3. Utilize existing Department resources and related programs;
2 and
3 4. Cooperate with the State Department of Education and the
4 Oklahoma State University Oklahoma Cooperative Extension Service as
5 needed in development and operation of the program; provided,
6 however, the Oklahoma Department of Agriculture, Food, and Forestry
7 shall have sole authority over the program.
8 C. The Oklahoma Department of Agriculture, Food, and Forestry
9 may provide incentives if funds are available to teachers who
10 participate in the Ag in the Classroom Education Program and utilize
11 curriculum provided by the program. Teachers who complete
12 eligibility requirements for the incentives as promulgated by rules
13 of the State Board of Agriculture may receive incentives. The
14 incentives may include but not be limited to:
15 1. Teacher recognition in newsletters, the Ag in the Classroom
16 website, social media, or other methods of recognition for
17 completing eligibility requirements;
18 2. A monetary award to be used for agriculture-related class
19 projects or field trips;
20 3. Entering a teacher into a drawing for Ag in the Classroom
21 resources or other items; and
22 4. Awarding a teacher an Ag in the Classroom certificate.
23 D. The Department shall directly receive all funds provided for
24 the Ag in the Classroom Education Program pursuant to Section 1104.3
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - SB1410 SFLR Page 2
